com.martinandersson.money.lib

Enum NumberFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<NumberFactory>
      • com.martinandersson.money.lib.NumberFactory
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<NumberFactory>

    public enum NumberFactory
extends java.lang.Enum<NumberFactory>
    Factory of Json numbers.

    This type will delegate all number construction to the "real" factory methods used by JSONP - yes, we have a hard coded dependency on JSONP.

    If you need "real world data", then use AppleData instead.
